Putin Prefers German Cars, Drives Audi One Week, BMW the Next

-- B y   M a r i n a   S y s o y e v a
-- 
2011-04-13T12:01:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-13/putin-prefers-german-cars-drives-audi-one-week-bmw-the-next.html
Russian Prime Minister  Vladimir Putin  said he enjoys driving German cars, alternating between Audi
and BMW models.  “I drive an Audi one week and a BMW the next week,” Putin
said during a meeting with Bavarian Premier Horst Seehofer and
German executives in Moscow today, according to Putin’s website.
“It’s a privilege to drive good cars.”  Putin personally owns four vehicles, three Russian-made
cars and a trailer he inherited from his father, according to an
income declaration posted on his website. Putin, a KGB operative
in  Germany  during the  Cold War , speaks fluent German.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marina Sysoyeva in Moscow 
 msysoyeva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
